\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775897375442,"end":1775897375449}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897378367,"sessionID":"ses_28444dcffffeVsazahFTZhj6mv","part":{"id":"prt_d7bbb73690011vXndCa5KGrbi1","messageID":"msg_d7bbb3db5001xO4Foc1GbRCaEH","sessionID":"ses_28444dcffffeVsazahFTZhj6mv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ea90678fe73a4e988c4171d5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-038: Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) — Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager` | **Language:** Go | **Size:** L\n4: **Base specs:** `pkg/workloadmanager/` source code\n5: **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## T-1: handler/sandbox_create.go — CreateSandboxRequest validation\n10: \n11: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create_test.go`\n12: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — valid request passes\n13: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — empty `Name` returns error\n14: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — empty `Namespace` returns error\n15: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — empty `Kind` returns error\n16: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — missing required `Template` fields returns error\n17: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — invalid port range (negative, >65535) returns error\n18: - [ ] Test `generateSessionID()` — returns valid UUID format\n19: - [ ] Test `generateSessionID()` — uniqueness across multiple calls\n20: - [ ] Test `generateSandboxName()` — follows naming convention with prefix + random suffix\n21: - [ ] Test `RandString(n)` — returns string of exact length `n`\n22: - [ ] Test `RandString(n)` — contains only alphanumeric characters\n23: - [ ] Test `getPortsOrDefaults()` — uses template ports when present\n24: - [ ] Test `getPortsOrDefaults()` — applies defaults when template ports are empty\n25: - [ ] Test `getPortsOrDefaults()` — mixed: some ports specified, others defaulted\n26: - [ ] Target: 90%+ coverage for validation and utility functions\n27: \n28: ## T-2: handler/sandbox_create.go — CR building logic\n29: \n30: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — builds valid AgentRuntime CR with all fields\n31: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — labels include `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by=agentcube`\n32: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — labels include session-id and workload-name\n33: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — annotations include idle-timeout when specified\n34: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — entry points populated from request\n35: - [ ] Test `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR()` — builds valid CodeInterpreter CR\n36: - [ ] Test `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR()` — warm pool branch: sets warm pool annotations/labels\n37: - [ ] Test `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR()` — non-warm-pool branch: omits warm pool fields\n38: - [ ] Test `buildEntryPoints()` — converts port specs to EntryPoint slice\n39: - [ ] Test `buildEntryPoints()` — handles empty ports list\n40: - [ ] Target: 85%+ coverage for CR building functions\n41: \n42: ## T-3: handler/sandbox_create.go — PicoD auth and Pod IP resolution\n43: \n44: - [ ] Test `injectPicodAuthEnv()` — injects identity secret env vars into container spec\n45: - [ ] Test `injectPicodAuthEnv()` — uses correct secret name `picod-router-identity` and key `public.pem`\n46: - [ ] Test `injectPicodAuthEnv()` — handles containers with existing env vars (appends, not replaces)\n47: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — resolves IP from `AnnotationSandboxPodName` annotation when pod exists\n48: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — resolves IP from label selector when annotation is missing\n49: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — returns empty string when no pod found\n50: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — handles pod without IP assigned (pending state)\n51: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — uses fake dynamic client with test scheme\n52: - [ ] Target: 85%+ coverage for auth injection and IP resolution\n53: \n54: ## T-4: handler/sandbox_create.go — HTTP handler integration\n55: \n56: - [ ] Test `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` HTTP handler — valid request returns 201 with sandbox info\n57: - [ ] Test `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` — invalid JSON body returns 400\n58: - [ ] Test `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` — validation failure returns 400 with error details\n59: - [ ] Test `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` — store create error returns 500\n60: - [ ] Test `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox()` — valid request returns 201\n61: - [ ] Test `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox()` — invalid kind returns 400\n62: - [ ] Test `rollbackCR()` — deletes CR on creation failure, logs error if rollback also fails\n63: - [ ] Test `SandboxCreateHandler` constructor — initializes with required dependencies\n64: - [ ] Test response body matches `CreateSandboxResponse` JSON structure\n65: - [ ] Target: 80%+ coverage for HTTP handlers\n66: \n67: ## T-5: handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go — GC orphan CR cleanup\n68: \n69: - [ ] Add tests to `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_lifecycle_test.go`\n70: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — finds and deletes CRs without corresponding sandbox entries\n71: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — skips CRs that have valid sandbox entries\n72: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — handles empty store (no CRs to clean)\n73: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — respects `MaxOrphanScanLimit`\n74: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — records orphan cleanup metric on deletion\n75: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — handles lister error gracefully (logs, does not panic)\n76: - [ ] Test `cleanupGhostEntries()` — removes store entries for non-existent CRs\n77: - [ ] Test `cleanupGhostEntries()` — skips entries with valid CRs\n78: - [ ] Test `cleanupGhostEntries()` — handles empty store\n79: - [ ] Test `cleanupGhostEntries()` — records ghost entry cleanup metric\n80: - [ ] Target: 85%+ coverage for orphan/ghost cleanup\n81: \n82: ## T-6: handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go — TTL/idle calculation and deletion\n83: \n84: - [ ] Test `calculateTimeToIdle()` — returns correct duration from last-activity annotation\n85: - [ ] Test `calculateTimeToIdle()` — handles missing annotation (uses creation time)\n86: - [ ] Test `calculateTimeToIdle()` — handles invalid annotation format (falls back to creation time)\n87: - [ ] Test `parseIdleTimeoutFromAnnotations()` — parses valid idle timeout annotation\n88: - [ ] Test `parseIdleTimeoutFromAnnotations()` — returns default when annotation missing\n89: - [ ] Test `parseIdleTimeoutFromAnnotations()` — returns default when annotation is invalid\n90: - [ ] Test `extractIdleTimeoutFromCR()` — extracts from CR annotations\n91: - [ ] Test `extractIdleTimeoutFromCR()` — returns default for CR without annotation\n92: - [ ] Test `isIdleExpired()` — returns true when idle timeout exceeded\n93: - [ ] Test `isIdleExpired()` — returns false when within idle timeout\n94: - [ ] Test `isIdleExpired()` — boundary: exact idle timeout moment (not yet expired)\n95: - [ ] Test `deleteSandbox()` — deletes sandbox and records metric\n96: - [ ] Test `deleteSandbox()` — handles delete error gracefully\n97: - [ ] Test `resolveGVR()` — returns correct GVR for each of 4 kinds (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Sandbox, SandboxClaim)\n98: - [ ] Test `resolveGVR()` — returns error for unknown kind\n99: - [ ] Target: 90%+ coverage for TTL/idle logic\n100: \n101: ## T-7: reconciler/types.go — constants and interface tests\n102: \n103: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/types_test.go`\n104: - [ ] Test resource type constants are distinct non-empty strings\n105: - [ ] Test result constants (`resultSuccess`, `resultError`) are distinct\n106: - [ ] Test error type constants are distinct and descriptive\n107: - [ ] Test status constants (`StatusPending`, `StatusRunning`, `StatusTerminated`) are distinct\n108: - [ ] Test `maxRetries`, `defaultWorkers`, `cacheSyncTimeout`, `shutdownTimeout` have expected values\n109: - [ ] Test `Store` interface methods exist (via compilation check in integration tests)\n110: - [ ] Test `ReconcilerDeps` struct fields are correctly typed\n111: - [ ] Target: 100% coverage for constants\n112: \n113: ## T-8: reconciler/metrics.go — metric recording methods\n114: \n115: - [ ] Extend `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics_test.go`\n116: - [ ] Test `IncReconcileTotal()` — increments counter with correct labels\n117: - [ ] Test `IncReconcileTotal()` — different result types (success/error) recorded separately\n118: - [ ] Test `ObserveReconcileDuration()` — records duration histogram with correct labels\n119: - [ ] Test `IncReconcileErrors()` — increments error counter with error type label\n120: - [ ] Test `IncReconcileErrors()` — different error types recorded separately\n121: - [ ] Test `SetWorkqueueDepth()` — sets gauge to current depth value\n122: - [ ] Test `IncWorkqueueAdds()` — increments workqueue adds counter\n123: - [ ] Test `NewPrometheusMetricsRecorder(nil)` — returns recorder without panic (nil registerer)\n124: - [ ] Test `NewPrometheusMetricsRecorder(nonNil)` — registers all metrics successfully\n125: - [ ] Test all metric methods on nil receiver — no panic (nil safety)\n126: - [ ] Target: 90%+ coverage for metrics recorder\n127: \n128: ## T-9: reconciler/sync.go — workqueue processing\n129: \n130: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sync_test.go`\n131: - [ ] Test `determineResourceType()` — returns `resourceTypeAgentRuntime` for AgentRuntime object\n132: - [ ] Test `determineResourceType()` — returns `resourceTypeCodeInterpreter` for CodeInterpreter object\n133: - [ ] Test `determineResourceType()` — returns `resourceTypePod` for Pod object\n134: - [ ] Test `determineResourceType()` — returns empty for unknown GVK\n135: - [ ] Test `processNextWorkItem()` — processes item successfully, forgets from 